result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeffrey E Fritz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
The defendant is to have NO CONTACT with A. Nelson and/or M. Jackson-Turner.

Defendant is to comply with any rules/recommendations as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.   Defendant to complete a Anger Management Program together with any follow through counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent. Defendant is to continue his treatment and follow through with any recommendations by Dr. Stephen Dal Cerro.   DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.   Defendant may petition for early termination of probation term after completion of 12 months, provided request is joined by agent and all financial obligations are paid in full and all treatment programming is completed.

records.addlTxt: 10:07 am cases called- 15CM136 & 15CM203. Defendant Jeffrey E Fritz in court with attorney Scott M Engstrom.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached and stated on the record.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest to Counts 1 & 2 of 15CM203.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in 15CM136. Sentencing argument by ADA Anderson. Sentencing argument by Attorney Engstrom. Statement by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places on probation for a period of 18 months. 1 day credit if revoked. CONDITIONS: No Contact with A. Nelson and/or M. Jackson-Turner. Anger Management Program and follow through. Follow through with any counseling or treatment with Dr. Stephen DalCerro or his treatment successor. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Court orders bond on file to be applied. Terms of Agent. Court will allow petition for early termination after 12 months, with recommendation of supervising agent. Appeal Rights Given.
